<TITLE> DU student died of wounds by brickbats: DMP </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Feb 5 (bdnews24.com)  Dhaka University student Abu Bakar on Wednesday died of wounds caused by brickbats and not by teargas shell, Dhaka metropolitan police commissioner AKM Shahidul Huq claimed on Friday. Bakar died at Dhaka Medical College Hospital at 9:30am on Wednesday. He was admitted to the hospital after he was injured along with 25 other students during a clash between BCL rival groups at Sir F Rahman Hall on Tuesday. Police fired tear gas to bring the situation under control. Witnesse, mostly his classmates, claimed that Bakar was hit by a teargas shell. Citing preliminary police report, Huq told reporters at his office on Friday that there was no sign of bullet injuries on Bakar's body. He further said that more information could be obtained after interrogating those who were arrested in connection with the tragic incident. bdn
